### Coordinating the Use of Application Profiles for EDHOC
**Presenter:** Marco Tiloca
* **Slides:** [03-20260720-lake-draft-ietf-lake-app-profiles](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-lake-20260720-lake-draft-ietf-lake-app-profiles-01)
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-lake-app-profiles`
* **Post-WGLC Updates (v08):**
  * **uprof Clarifications:** Clarified the purpose of the `uprof` parameter across CBOR maps, web links, and DNS resource records.
  * **Session-Specific Advertisement:** Added text explaining the benefits of advertising application profiles during active sessions (it operates with a low implementation bar, allows client-only advertisements, and enables session-specific parameters).
  * **CDDL Improvements:** Enhanced CDDL socket extensibility using regex rules. Added high-level descriptions of registered well-known profiles.
  * **Error Codes & Security:** Enhanced error code semantics to allow the sender to report both supported application profiles and a descriptive error string. Addressed security considerations regarding persisting learned profile information.
  * **Resumption:** Added a boolean parameter to explicitly indicate support for PSK resumption.

